            "content": "# CLAUDE.md\n\nThis file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.\n\n## Project Overview\n\nEducational workshop demonstrating AI application security using Google Cloud Model Armor. A Node.js/Express chat app backed by Vertex AI (Gemini) with a vanilla JS frontend. Model Armor screens both user prompts (input) and model responses (output) for malicious content, prompt injection, and data leakage.\n\n## Commands\n\nAll commands run from the `app/` directory:\n\n```bash\nnpm install          # Install dependencies\nnpm run dev          # Dev server with --watch auto-reload (port 8080)\nnpm start            # Production server\n```\n\nDeploy to Cloud Run:\n```bash\ngcloud builds submit --tag <region>-docker.pkg.dev/<project>/<repo>/secure-chat-app\ngcloud run deploy secure-chat-app --image <image-tag> --set-env-vars \"...\"\n```\n\nNo test suite exists in this project.\n\n## Required Environment Variables\n\nCreate `app/.env` with:\n- `GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT` — GCP project ID\n- `GOOGLE_CLOUD_LOCATION` — Region (e.g., `us-central1`)\n- `MODEL_ARMOR_TEMPLATE` — Full resource path: `projects/.../locations/.../templates/<name>`\n- `MODEL_ID` — Optional, defaults to `gemini-2.5-flash`\n\n## Architecture\n\n**Single API endpoint:** `POST /api/chat` in `app/server.js`\n\nRequest flow:\n1. Receive user message + `useModelArmor` boolean flag\n2. If Model Armor enabled → sanitize user prompt via `ModelArmorClient.sanitizeUserPrompt()`\n3. Call Gemini with system instruction + contents of `knowledgebase.txt` as context\n4. If Model Armor enabled → sanitize model response via `ModelArmorClient.sanitizeModelResponse()`\n5. Return response (or blocked message if filtered)\n\n**Frontend:** `app/public/` — vanilla HTML/CSS/JS chat UI with a toggle to enable/disable Model Armor. No build step.\n\n**Key dependencies:** `@google-cloud/modelarmor`, `@google/genai`, `express`, `dotenv`\n\n## Workshop Context\n\nThe codebase intentionally includes sensitive mock data in `knowledgebase.txt` and a \"secret passphrase\" in the system prompt to demonstrate prompt injection and data leakage vulnerabilities. This is by design for the workshop — do not \"fix\" these as security issues.\n\nWorkshop steps are documented in `docs/codelab.md` (Claat format).\n",
