            "content": "# Custom Domain for Cloud Run Static Sites\n\nHow to point a custom domain (e.g., `secure-ai.uvishere.com`) to a Cloud Run service hosting a static site (e.g., a Claat codelab).\n\n## Context\n\nDeployed a static codelab site to Cloud Run using `--source .` with an nginx container. Needed to map a custom domain to it.\n\nCloud Run URL: `workshop-codelab-404138281426.us-central1.run.app`\nDesired domain: `secure-ai.uvishere.com` (DNS managed by Cloudflare)\n\n## Options Explored\n\n### Option 1: GCS Bucket Website Hosting\n\nHost static files in a Cloud Storage bucket named after the domain.\n\n```bash\ngcloud storage buckets create gs://secure-ai.uvishere.com --project $PROJECT_ID --location us-central1 --uniform-bucket-level-access\n# Upload files, make bucket public\n# CNAME secure-ai.uvishere.com -> c.storage.googleapis.com\n```\n\n**Blocker:** Requires domain ownership verification via Google Search Console (TXT record). Straightforward but adds a verification step.\n\n### Option 2: Cloud Run Domain Mapping\n\nUse Cloud Run's built-in domain mapping feature.\n\n```bash\ngcloud run domain-mappings create --service workshop-codelab --domain secure-ai.uvishere.com --region us-central1\n```\n\nThen add the DNS records it outputs to Cloudflare. Simplest GCP-native option.\n\n### Option 3: GCP Load Balancer\n\nFull load balancer setup in front of Cloud Run:\n\n1. Serverless NEG pointing to Cloud Run service\n2. Backend service with the NEG attached\n3. Google-managed SSL certificate for the domain\n4. URL map + HTTPS proxy + global forwarding rule\n5. A record in Cloudflare pointing to the LB IP\n\nMost flexible but overkill for a static site.\n\n### Option 4: Cloudflare Worker Proxy (chosen)\n\nA Cloudflare Worker that proxies requests to Cloud Run, rewriting the Host header.\n\n```javascript\nexport default {\n  async fetch(request) {\n    const url = new URL(request.url);\n    url.hostname = \"workshop-codelab-404138281426.us-central1.run.app\";\n    return fetch(url.toString(), {\n      method: request.method,\n      headers: request.headers,\n    });\n  },\n};\n```\n\nSetup:\n1. Create a Worker in Cloudflare dashboard (Workers & Pages → Create → Worker)\n2. Paste the script, deploy it\n3. Go to worker Settings → Triggers → Custom Domains\n4. Add `secure-ai.uvishere.com`\n\n**Why this works:** Cloud Run expects the Host header to match its service URL. A plain CNAME would send the custom domain as the Host header, which Cloud Run rejects. The Worker forwards the request with the correct hostname.\n\n**Why not a plain CNAME:** Cloudflare CNAME to the Cloud Run URL fails because the Host header is `secure-ai.uvishere.com` instead of the Cloud Run service URL.\n\n## Gotcha: Corporate DNS\n\nWhen testing with `nslookup`, the domain resolved to a corporate proxy (Incapsula/pageup.com.au) instead of Cloudflare — corporate networks may intercept DNS. Test from outside the corporate network to verify.\n",
